    {
      "_id": "5i3gAqCCdCANZcpa",
      "name": "Plague Cloud (Recharge after a Short or Long Rest)",
      "type": "feat",
      "system": {
        "source": {
          "custom": "",
          "book": "GHMG",
          "page": "257",
          "license": ""
        },
        "description": {
          "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>The pesta creates a 20-foot-radius cloud of yellowish mist centered on a point it chooses within 60 feet of it. This mist spreads around corners and lightly obscures its area. The cloud lingers for 1 minute, until the pesta's @status[concentration] ends (as if @status[concentration||concentrating] on a spell), or until strong wind disperses the cloud.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>When a creature enters the area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, that creature must make a [[/save ability=constitution dc=14]] saving throw. The creature takes 22 ([[/damage 4d10 type=poison]]) damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. Someone who fails the saving throw is also &amp;Reference[condition=poisoned] and subjected to the pesta's disease (often @disease[sewer plague]). Creatures are affected even if they hold their breath or don't need to breathe. A creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the &amp;Reference[condition=poisoned] condition on itself on a success. The disease remains until cured.</p></div>",
          "chat": ""
        },
